      • progressReport

        protected void progressReport(Shell shell,
                  boolean force,
                  java.lang.String str,
                  java.lang.Object... obj)
        Generates a progress report if appropriate. The progress report is only written if timing is correct (or if forcing is performed) and if progress reports are active (non-zero delay).
        Parameters:
        shell - The shell to which to write the report.
        force - true to force this message to be written regardless of timing; false otherwise.
        str - The string to format for the report.
        obj - The objects to format into the report string.
